## After editing — sanity steps DEV must run

1. `rm -rf .next` — force Turbopack cache rebuild (file deletes corrupt the cache).
2. `npx tsc --noEmit` — must pass. If it complains about `routing.locales.includes(savedLocale as any)` anywhere else in the codebase, leave it — we didn't change that pattern. Our middleware uses `(typeof routing.locales)[number]` as the stricter type.
3. Visual check on dev server:
   - Visit `/` — English, no redirect, cookie written (BINAYAH_LOCALE=en).
   - Click nav → Chinese — URL becomes `/zh/`, all nav labels in Chinese, cookie=zh.
   - Click nav → Arabic — URL becomes `/ar/`, layout flips RTL (logo on right, nav on left), text in Arabic.
   - Click nav → English — URL becomes `/` (no prefix), cookie=en, everything in English.
   - Visit `/ru/about` directly (simulating a shared URL) — renders /ru/about, does NOT become `/ru/ru/about` or similar double-prefix.
   - Visit `/zh/project/sensia-by-beyond` — renders, no double-prefix.

## Acceptance criteria (what QA will verify)

1. **Locale set is exactly `[en, ru, zh, ar]`.** No `kz`, no `in` anywhere (routing.ts, middleware, Navbar, messages/).
2. **`messages/kz.json` and `messages/in.json` no longer exist.**
3. **Language switcher works**: clicking any of the 4 languages in the Navbar dropdown navigates to the correct URL (`/` for en, `/ru`, `/zh`, `/ar`) and the page content changes language WITHOUT a full page reload flicker that lands on a 404.
4. **English persists after switching from a non-English locale**: user on /ru/about clicks English → URL becomes /about, page is English, cookie BINAYAH_LOCALE=en is set, refreshing the page keeps them on English (no bounce back to /ru/).
5. **No double-prefix 404s**: visiting `/ru/about`, `/zh/contact`, `/ar/valuation` directly (e.g. from a shared link) all render correctly. `/zh/admin/[token]` (or any admin token containing ascii chars) does not get additional locale prefix prepended.
6. **RTL**: when locale=ar, `<html dir="rtl">` is set (inspect element). Navbar logo appears on the right, nav items flow right-to-left.
7. **Translations applied**: homepage hero title, nav labels (Buy/Rent/Off-Plan/etc), footer tagline, contact page title & form labels all display in the active locale for en/ru/zh/ar. No English leakage in translated keys.
8. **Cookie always written**: after any switch or first visit, `BINAYAH_LOCALE` cookie is present with the correct value (including `en`).
9. **TypeScript compiles clean** (`npx tsc --noEmit`).
10. **No console errors** on page load for any of the 4 locales.

## Forbidden
- Do NOT modify `src/navigation.ts` — the generic `createNavigation(routing)` picks up the new locales automatically.
- Do NOT add hreflang meta tags — out of scope.
- Do NOT translate admin pages or API-sourced content — out of scope.
- Do NOT add next/navigation imports — the Navbar already uses `@/navigation` which is correct.
- Do NOT add new UI components, buttons, or styling. This is a logic + translations stage only.
- Do NOT add SEO redirects from old `/kz/*` and `/in/*` URLs — out of scope per plannerOutput.
- Do NOT add per-component RTL logic (e.g., conditional `flex-row-reverse`). The `dir='rtl'` on `<html>` is sufficient for this stage; CSS logical properties are only needed for any NEW layout, and we aren't adding new layouts here.
- Do NOT change `localePrefix: 'as-needed'` — keep `as-needed`.

## Demo path
1. Open browser in incognito, visit `http://localhost:3000/` — English renders, cookie=en written.
2. Click the globe icon in the navbar, select 中文 — URL becomes `/zh`, nav labels become 购买/租赁/期房, cookie=zh.
3. Click globe → العربية — URL becomes `/ar`, page flips RTL, Arabic text throughout.
4. Click globe → English — URL becomes `/`, English, cookie=en.
5. Hard-refresh (Cmd-Shift-R) — stays on English (does not bounce to /ru or geo-locale) because cookie=en.
6. In another incognito window, set the `BINAYAH_LOCALE=ru` cookie manually, visit `/ru/about` — renders /ru/about with Russian content, URL stays /ru/about (no double /ru/ru/).
7. Visit `/zh/projects/sensia-by-beyond` — project page renders, URL stays as-is, no 404.

